{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Line a baking sheet with a silicone mat, generously dust with confectioners sugar and set aside.","Place sugar, corn syrup and water into mixing bowl and cook <b>5 min\/212°F\/speed 2<b>.","Add butter and cook <b>9 min\/250°F\/speed 2<b>.","Add confectioners sugar, milk powder, salt and vanilla and mix <b>1 min\/speed 3.5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix a further <b>1 min\/speed 3.5<b>. Quickly transfer mixture to prepared baking sheet. Let rest until cool enough to handle (approx. 10 min.).","Divide dough into 3 pieces (approx. 4.5 oz ea.). The first piece remains white. For the second piece, add 5 drops yellow food coloring and with gloves (see Tip), knead until fully incorporated. Dust with confectioners sugar, as needed if dough becomes too soft or sticky. For the third piece, add 7 drops yellow food coloring and 3 drops orange food coloring and knead until fully incorporated.","Pinch or cut an equal sized piece of dough from each of the three colors. Roll each color into a rope (approx. ¼ in. thick). Lay ropes side by side (yellow, orange, then white) to form a strip. Gently press together so they stick. Lightly flatten to smooth out edges. Cut candy into small triangles and continue with remaining dough.","Toss Candy Corn with corn starch, as needed to prevent sticking. Let rest on parchment until dry (approx. 2 hr.- overnight). Serve or store in an airtight container with parchment between each layer to prevent sticking."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["8 oz confectioners sugar, sifted, plus extra to dust","4 oz sugar","3 ½ oz corn syrup","½ oz water","1 oz unsalted butter, in pieces","1 oz skim milk powder","&frac18; tsp salt","½ tsp vanilla extract","12 drops yellow food coloring, divided","3 drops orange food coloring","2 oz corn starch, to toss"]}],"id":"r408840","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-NZ_fzON0W54\/XZWc7b1qnNI\/AAAAAAAAegs\/vCigcQ75UeohWjA814fq-9Hj-rsev54mgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_8tJTHiuhDeLO3Yes.png","title":"Candy Corn","publishedAt":"2018-10-19T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"0 g","fat":"0 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"8 g","calories":"146 kJ \/ 35 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking sheet, silicone mat, disposable vinyl gloves, parchment paper, airtight container","hintsAndTricks":["Wear disposable gloves when kneading dough to prevent staining. Knead against parchment or a baking mat to avoid staining countertop or work surface."],"basicInfo":["medium","45m","3h 10m","60 pieces"]}